<h2 id="interlude-power-chord-strumming">Interlude power chord strumming</h2>

<p>Finally, we have this â€œpower chordâ€ rock-out section of the interlude, which involves heavy use of the D power chord. This is characterized by a loud, rapid â€œdown-up-down-up-downâ€ strumming pattern, which is followed by a moment of silence before repeating again.</p>

